ETC: Exact Topological Computing
=================================
Installation and Verification Guide

REQUIREMENTS
------------
  Python  >= 3.9  
  sympy   >= 1.12
  mpmath  >= 1.3.0

  Optional for Lean 4 proof checking:
    Lean 4 and Mathlib4 -- install from leanprover.github.io
    Lean is NOT a Python package; cannot be installed via pip.

INSTALLATION
------------
  pip install .
  pip install ".[dev]"     # adds pytest, black, mypy, flake8

  Verify:
  python -c "import etc; print(etc.__version__)"   # 0.1.0

RUNNING THE TEST SUITE
----------------------
  pytest tests/ -v
  # All 88 tests should pass.
  # A reference capture of this output is in tests/expected/expected_output.txt

RUNNING THE COMPARISON SCRIPT
------------------------------
  python scripts/run_comparison.py
  # Reproduces Table 1 (float64 vs ETC on all seven canonical problems)

RUNNING THE BENCHMARK
---------------------
  python scripts/benchmark.py
  # Reproduces Tables 3-6 of the paper (~5-15 seconds)

PACKAGE STRUCTURE
-----------------
ETC/
  etc/
    __init__.py
    py.typed
    certified.py
    core/         real.py, sign.py, complex.py, integer.py, interval.py
    geometry/     curves.py, polygon.py, surfaces.py
    topology/     space.py, path.py, homotopy.py, invariants.py, manifold.py
    analysis/     series.py, calculus.py, ode.py
    verify/       certificate.py, formal.py, symbolic.py, lean_syntax.py
    problems/     base.py, registry.py, canonical_problems.py
  tests/
    test_core.py
    test_problems.py
    expected/expected_output.txt
    portability/   (saved cross-platform run transcripts; not pytest-collected)
  scripts/
    benchmark.py
    run_comparison.py
  doc/
    manual.pdf      (pre-built; ships in this package, not regenerated by a script)
  pyproject.toml  README.md  INSTALL  LICENSE

